Here I'll show a series of visualizations I made of covid cases at colleges in the US

Note that this data is out of date, circa 10/20/2020, and that this is from a project I worked on last semester. Keep in mind that as there is no national standard for collecting this data, different colleges qualify their total cases differently. For example, some colleges remove students who recover from their case counts.

The next slide shows the covid case counts at colleges through the US. The size and color of the dot corresponds to the number of cases at the college.

The next slide shows shows the states’ Covid performance on the left plot, and each colleges’ Covid performance on the right plot. If you select a particular state, the right plot will filter to college within that state. On the left plot, each dot represents a state. The size of the dot represents that state’s population and its color represents the proportion of total cases to its population. On the right plot, each dot represents a college. The size and color of those dots represents its total cases.

For embeding this visualizations within this deck, I simply made the visualizations using Python and the Altair module. Once the visualization was completed, I exported the viz to html and used the autogenerated html code for embedding it within the deck.
These visualizations essentially show that some states and colleges are handling covid better than others. Some colleges make a up a pretty big percentage of their states covid cases while in other states, universities barely make a dent in the state's cases.
